			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Addendum to above.<BR>
<BR>
Yes I know it should be column of frost.(doh!)<BR>
Also if soloing one creature(and I dont know of <BR>
any living casters deliberately soloing more than<BR>
1 creature at a time of any real strength) You can<BR>
cast root on the creature, followed by firestorm,<BR>
and the 3 waves of damage will probably just be<BR>
about done by the time you have cast two shock of<BR>
lightnings on whatever it was.  Stick a fork in it<BR>
folks 78+78+84(28*3). 240 pts of damage in 4 <BR>
clicks and for 212 mana. You still have enough <BR>
mana for a coup de grace spell like shock of ice,<BR>
or a firebolt, or if you have high intelligence<BR>
perhaps another shock of lightning.  Excellent <BR>
against caster because taking damage from sub<BR>
sequent waves from firestorm should mess up their<BR>
casting, and 240 pnts of damage should bury a <BR>
level 12 caster...it would me unless I resisted.<BR>
<BR>
So you can use firestorm solo against one mob, but<BR>
the rest are a waste on 1 mob.<BR>
<BR>
Draconius<BR>
12th Wizard<BR>
Lanys T'vyl Server...Give me a tell!!!<BR>

