	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				On AoE Spells!!!<BR>
<BR>
Yeah I like them, alot! This is the type of spell<BR>
that will benefit you the caster and your party<BR>
more than any other spell in a GROUP setting.<BR>
<BR>
I am 12th and so far the column of ice spell is <BR>
best against 3 or 4 opponents, and firestorm is <BR>
against 2.  Have not got frost spiral yet but if<BR>
it works like other AoE here is a breakdown at <BR>
level 12.<BR>
<BR>
Column of Ice vs 2 mobs 60/39=1.53<BR>
&quot;             vs 3 mobs 90/39=2.30<BR>
&quot;             vs 4 mobs 120/39=3.07<BR>
(very rare will you have 4 in range, will tell you<BR>
how to max targets in a sec)<BR>
<BR>
Firestorm     vs 2 mobs 112/62=1.8<BR>
(it can hit both mobs twice for 28 each at this <BR>
lvl max)<BR>
&quot;             vs 3 mobs  84/62=1.35<BR>
if one dies in first pass  112/62= 1.8<BR>
&quot;             vs 4 mobs  112/62=1.8<BR>
<BR>
Frost Spiral  vs 2 mobs 78/100=.78<BR>
Frost Spiral  vs 3 mobs 117/100=1.17<BR>
Frost Spiral  vs 4 mobs 156/100=1.56<BR>
(Yes this spell stinks unless you hit 4 mobs,<BR>
and less mobs than that its more mana inefficient<BR>
than shock spells)<BR>
<BR>
Shock of Lightning 78/60= 1.3<BR>
Shock of Ice        38/30=1.26<BR>
Shock of Fire       16/15=1.06<BR>
Fire Bolt           48/40=1.20<BR>
<BR>
As you can see the DD spells are more mana <BR>
inefficent than the AoE spells. Also I believe<BR>
only Wizards get AoE spells at this level, we<BR>
need to take advantage of them to show people<BR>
why wizards are nice to have in a party.<BR>
<BR>
Now these are all ideals and assume noone resists<BR>
and that you do max damage with each.  This shows<BR>
the potential for a 12th level wizard.  <BR>
<BR>
The tactic I promised is simple...cast AoE on <BR>
your tank or other party member who is being <BR>
attacked by multiple opponents.  Fighting Bandits<BR>
in Karana I have very rarely pulled any bandits to<BR>
myself.  Don't use AoE solo gang, unless you have <BR>
a death wish or are fighting no xp greenies and <BR>
want to impress or save a newbie character who <BR>
is being chased.   Frost spiral will kill all four<BR>
fire beatles chasing that poor newbie, you'll make<BR>
a friend, and you'll feel good.   Besides it keeps<BR>
the guards from makin the kill. (I recommend you <BR>
collect the eyes and give them all to the poor<BR>
soul being chased, we were all newbies once!!)<BR>
<BR>
I hope this helps, and one more thing.  I was the<BR>
lowest and weakest character in all but one bandit<BR>
hunting group. Most were 13 or 14th level, I died<BR>
less often than the rest, and noone complained I<BR>
was not doing my job. AoE's helped us pull of <BR>
fights we never would have otherwise.  I do <BR>
recommend a full boat (6 member party) of 10-14th<BR>
level characters to increase survivability, but <BR>
the bandit farm northeast of T2 can be taken by <BR>
4 characters of this level successfully.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck and Good hunting!<BR>
Draconius<BR>
12th Wizard<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
